Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%oz} into 1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and mince half the
@yellow onion{1}; cut remaining onion into quarters. Trim, peel, and cut
@carrots{6%oz} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces.

Toss potatoes, quartered onion, and carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large
drizzle of @cooking oil{3%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack
until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; place between
2 large pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{}
until chicken is about ½ inch thick.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Season chicken all over with @garlic powder{1%tsp}, half the
@dried thyme{1%tsp}, ½ tsp salt (1 tsp for 4 servings), and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil (large drizzle for 4 servings) in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through,
~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{} and tent with #foil{} to keep
warm. Wipe out pan and let cool.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @cranberry jam{1}, 1 TBSP
water (2 TBSP for 4 servings), a pinch of remaining thyme, salt, and pepper.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in pan used for chicken over
medium heat. Add minced onion; cook, stirring, until softened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low. Sprinkle @flour{1%tbsp} over onion; whisk to combine. Stir
in ½ cup water (1 cup for 4) and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a
simmer and cook until thickened and saucy, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt
and pepper. Remove from heat.

While gravy cooks, halve and toast @brioche buns{2}.

Spread a thin layer of cranberry sauce onto cut sides of bottom buns. Fill
buns with chicken and top with as much gravy as you like (be sure to reserve
at least a couple spoonfuls for serving). Close sandwiches.

Divide sandwiches and potato-carrot jumble between plates. Serve with reserved
gravy for dipping.